LIMPOPO COPS have launched a massive manhunt for a group of
armed suspects who robbed a cash-intransit van on Saturday afternoon.Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said: "It is
alleged that the cash-in-transit van was travelling along the R40 road from
Accornhoek  towards Hoedspruit when the two
vehicles, a VW Amarok and Toyota Corolla with several occupants inside started
shooting at it until the driver lost control and it overturned."He said following that, the suspects blew up the van with
explosives  and took an undisclosed
